  abilityName: Warp & Weft
  description: "Swap the positions of an object you are\nholding and another object
    you can see. They\nmust be of a similar size and shape, such as\ntwo swords.\nPASSION
    - Detachment\nRestore SPI when you discard something that\nyou want.\nThis and
    that, might just be that and this\nAs now is morrow, perfectly amiss\nWeaver
    Knight\nUNUSUAL THROWN WEAPON\nDesign Ability\n1 Club +d6 in a duel\n2 Disc +d6
    vs steeds\n3 Spike +d6 vs fleeing targets\n4 Bola +d6 vs mounted\ntargets\n5
    Fork +d6 vs flying targets\n6 Ball +d6 vs targets without\na shield\nKNIGHTED
    BY...\nThe Armoured Seer\nVIG 15, CLA 7, SPI 9, 5 GD, A3 (metal body)\n\u2022
    A great blocky mass of chains and iron\nplates, just about humanoid in shape.\n\u2022
    They were interred in their armour after\na mortal wound, now seeing through
    the\neyes of every piece of armour and every\nweapon in the Realm.\n\u2022 Wants
    to restore their body to its\nprevious health.\nPerson: Thrifty herald ~ Name:
    Pryer ~ Characteristic: Animal lover\nObject: Seer arrow ~ Beast: Watcher python
    ~ State: Coveting ~ Theme: Hearing\n6\n7\nThe"
